# WT Multi SEO Pro — Code Review

## Overview

The plugin is well-structured: singleton pattern throughout, clear file separation, good use of WordPress hooks, PHP 8.0+ features, and consistent escaping. Overall the code quality is **solid**, but there are several **bugs, incomplete stubs, and minor security/performance issues** that should be addressed before the plugin runs in production.

---

## 🔴 Bugs / Broken Functionality

### 1. `PLSEO_Sitemap::maybe_flush()` — Flushes on *every* `save_post`
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-sitemap.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-sitemap.php) · line 466–468

```php
// Current (bad)
public function maybe_flush(): void {
    flush_rewrite_rules();
}
```

`flush_rewrite_rules()` is expensive and should almost never be called on `save_post` (runs every autosave, every revision, every quick-edit). It only needs to run when rewrite rules actually change (activation / deactivation). Remove this hook or replace with a smarter condition.

```php
// Better: remove the hook entirely from __construct, or guard it:
public function maybe_flush(): void {
    // Only flush when the sitemap rewrite rule isn't already registered
    global $wp_rewrite;
    if ( empty( $wp_rewrite->extra_rules_top['sitemap\\.xml$'] ) ) {
        flush_rewrite_rules();
    }
}
```

---

### 2. `PLSEO_Redirects::handle_old_slug_redirect()` — Empty Stub
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-redirects.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-redirects.php) · line 26–28

The method is registered as a `redirect_canonical` filter but just returns `$redirect_url` unchanged — it does nothing beyond what WordPress already does natively. If the `redirect_old_slugs` option is enabled by default (`true`), users expect this to work.

Either implement the logic (check `_wp_old_slug` post meta and redirect) or remove the option/hook until it's ready.

---

### 3. `PLSEO_Schema::add_local_business_to_graph()` — Empty Stub
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-schema.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-schema.php) · line 225

```php
private function add_local_business_to_graph(): void { /* Logic */ }
```

The admin UI has full Local Business fields (type, address, phone, hours) and the option `schema_local_business` can be enabled — but the method that outputs the schema is completely empty. This will silently produce no output when the feature is on.

