## 🟠 Performance Issues

### 10. [PLSEO_Columns](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/admin/class-plseo-columns.php#4-55) — Multiple `get_post_meta()` calls per row, no caching
**File:** [admin/class-plseo-columns.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/admin/class-plseo-columns.php)

Three separate `get_post_meta()` calls fire per row in the posts list. WordPress does warm the meta cache for listed posts, so this is fine in practice — but worth flagging as a pattern to watch.

---

### 11. [PLSEO_Sitemap](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-sitemap.php#14-485) — [get_post_images()](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-sitemap.php#396-437) runs `preg_match_all` on raw post content
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-sitemap.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-sitemap.php) · line 415

This regex runs against un-filtered post content. For large sites with block editor content, running regex over potentially hundreds of posts on each sitemap request adds up. Consider caching image results in a transient per post ID, or limiting further.

---

## 🔵 Missing Features / Improvements

### 12. `PLSEO_Options::sanitize_option()` — Generic callback for all options
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-options.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-options.php) · line 135

The [sanitize_option](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-options.php#132-144) callback is a single generic function registered for every option, but it doesn't know *which* option it's being called for. This means URL options (like `og_default_image`) are sanitized with `sanitize_text_field` instead of `esc_url_raw` — but those options are only saved through `PLSEO_Admin::save_settings()` which does type-aware sanitization. The [register_setting](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-options.php#112-131) callback path (REST API / [options.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-options.php) direct post) would miss the URL sanitization.

Fix: use a per-option sanitize closure that matches the type, or consolidate to just one save path.

---

### 13. No `noindex_empty_taxonomy` enforcement at runtime
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-meta.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-meta.php) / [includes/class-plseo-robots.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-robots.php)

The option `noindex_empty_taxonomy` exists in defaults and the admin UI, but [get_robots()](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-meta.php#125-170) in [PLSEO_Meta](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-meta.php#4-208) never checks it. Empty taxonomy archives will be indexed regardless.

```php
// Add inside get_robots():
if ( ( is_tax() || is_category() || is_tag() ) && PLSEO_Helpers::get_option( 'noindex_empty_taxonomy', true ) ) {
    $term = get_queried_object();
    if ( $term instanceof WP_Term && 0 === $term->count ) {
        return 'noindex, follow';
    }
}
```

---

### 14. [PLSEO_Hreflang](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-hreflang.php#4-110) — Archive pages (author, date, post-type) have no hreflang
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-hreflang.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-hreflang.php) · [get_hreflang_links()](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-hreflang.php#47-97)

The method handles singular, taxonomy, and front page — but not author/date/post-type archives. Those pages fall through and produce no hreflang tags, which is correct for non-translated archives but should be called out explicitly.

---

### 15. Social media options lack `social_facebook`, `social_twitter`, `social_linkedin`
**File:** [includes/class-plseo-schema.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-schema.php) · lines 111–115 & [includes/class-plseo-options.php](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Local%20Sites/demo/app/public/wp-content/plugins/wt-multi-seo-pro/includes/class-plseo-options.php)

The Schema class references:
```php
PLSEO_Helpers::get_option( 'social_facebook' ),
PLSEO_Helpers::get_option( 'social_twitter' ),
PLSEO_Helpers::get_option( 'social_linkedin' ),
```

But none of these keys exist in `PLSEO_Options::get_defaults()`, and the social Settings page only covers OG/Twitter Card — not sameAs profile URLs. Add these to defaults and the admin social settings page.

---

## ✅ What's Working Well

| Area | Notes |
|---|---|
| **Architecture** | Clean singleton pattern, consistent `ABSPATH` guard, proper hook priorities |
| **Escaping** | Nearly all output uses `esc_attr`, `esc_url`, `esc_html`, `esc_xml` correctly |
| **Hreflang** | Properly handles `zh_CN → zh-Hans` locale mapping, x-default logic is correct |
| **Canonical** | Correctly removes WP's built-in `rel_canonical`, handles HTTPS normalisation |
| **Sitemap** | Translation-set deduplication via fingerprint is an elegant pattern |
| **Metabox save** | Good nonce verification, autosave guard, capability check, type-aware sanitization |
| **Polylang integration** | All Polylang function calls are guarded with `function_exists()` |
| **Breadcrumbs** | Parent/ancestor traversal is correct for both posts and hierarchical terms |

---

